  "text": "The formation of mammalian ovarian follicular antrum and formation of follicular fluids are important processes in follicular development. The proportion of follicular fluid at maximum size varies from species to species. Generally, larger species such as human, bovine, ovine, equine, and porcine have larger follicles, with the fluid comprising a substantial proportion of the follicle volumes at ovulation (estimated at >95% in bovine). Smaller species such as rats and mice have smaller follicles with fractionally less follicular fluid [CITATION_1] .",
